## Steps

### step 1
id: open-profile-team
instruction: Click your profile icon or name in the top-right corner to open Profile settings, then click the "Team" section in the left navigation.
success_criteria: You are on the Team tab showing a list of current team members and an "Invite User" button. If you do not see this button, you may not have Admin role.
anchor: profile-team-tab
on_success: next
on_stuck: Profile is usually in the top-right corner. Once in Profile, look for "Team" in the left-hand navigation panel.

### step 2
id: click-invite-user
instruction: Click the "Invite User" button.
success_criteria: An invite dialog has opened with fields for email address and role selection (Biller or Admin).
anchor: invite-user-button
on_success: next
on_stuck: The Invite User button is on the Team page. Only Admins see this button — if it's missing, ask your Admin to send the invite.

### step 3
id: enter-email-and-role
instruction: Enter the new team member's email address. Select their role: choose "Biller" for billing staff who need access to claims and workflows, or "Admin" for supervisors who also need to manage team members and settings.
success_criteria: Email address is entered and a role is selected.
anchor: invite-email-field
on_success: next
on_stuck: Type the full email address in the email field, then click the role dropdown to choose Biller or Admin.

### step 4
id: generate-and-send-invite
instruction: Click to generate the invite link. Copy the link and send it to the new team member via email or your team's messaging app.
success_criteria: An invite link is displayed. The new team member appears in the Team list with a "Pending" badge until they accept.
anchor: generate-invite-link-button
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the generate/create button to get the link, then copy it and send it manually. If the link expires before the person uses it, generate a new one.

## Completion Message
invite sent! the new team member will use the link to set up their account. they'll show as "Pending" in your team list until they complete sign-up. if they don't receive it, just generate a fresh link from the same Team tab.

